Roscoe C. ZUCKERMAN, Appellant, v. Frank H. HOOD, an Individual and J. B. Schwag and J. W. Glenn, Individually and as Copartners Doing Business under the Firm Name and Style of Fred Schwab Commission Co., Appellees. No. 5897. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 4, 1930. Percy S. Webster, of Stockton, Cal., and David Livingston, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Charles M. Fryer, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before RUDKIN, DIETRICH, and WILBUR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
